column1: # The gauge and observer moved from the Boston High Street site in 1886 - the month of the move is not known, end of June assumed for allocating readings to sites.
# Mr Wheeler had the London Road house built in 1884-86, so the gauge move in 1886 mentioned on the 1880s sheet seems to be to the new house.
# The London Road house matches the directions to St Thomas's church on the 1900s sheet.
